          "text": "Location: Tennessee<p>Remote Yes (open to on-prem)<p>Willing to relocate: Yes (To Netherlands only.)<p>Technologies: Kubernetes, EKS, RKE, Rancher, Argo (CD and Workflows), GitLab CI&#x2F;CD, Python, general AWS, and more.<p>Résumé: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;drive.google.com&#x2F;file&#x2F;d&#x2F;1kjyLcuHblAVmxEXXUj3hEjjS7jlYQF82&#x2F;view?usp=share_link\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;drive.google.com&#x2F;file&#x2F;d&#x2F;1kjyLcuHblAVmxEXXUj3hEjjS7jl...</a><p>Email: h@hhh.hn<p>I&#x27;ve been designing and building enterprise platforms for device management, kubernetes management, and for IaC atop of Gitlab for the last 3 years with a focus on providing painkillers for all of our customers. This has grown into hundreds of sites, thousands of applications, and thousands of IoT devices (RPi, Jetsen, etc.) and thousands of servers.<p>Along with this, we&#x27;ve been baking in tooling into these platforms, giving application developers easier access to cloud resources both in AWS and on-prem, removing effort for logging&#x2F;observability&#x2F;alerting, and more.<p>I have many passions and would love to chat about what you&#x27;re working on. Only so much can fit in a bio or a resume :)",
